subsection.def:
Commissioner (局長) means the Commissioner of Inland
                Revenue appointed under the Inland Revenue Ordinance (Cap.
                    112);

paragraph.content:
an open-ended fund company, its registered office;
                            (Replaced 14 of 2020 s.
                            113)

subparagraph.content:
that is not otherwise liable to be registered under this Ordinance;
                            (Amended 16 of 2016 s.
                            36)

the application is made under section 79 of the Limited
                        Partnership Fund Ordinance (Cap. 637);
                        and

paragraph.content:
the business carried on by the applicant is registered, or deemed to have
                    been registered, under section 6 (matter);
                    and

the application is made by an open-ended fund company for registration by a
                    name that is not the name of the company;
                    or

subparagraph.content:
the date of commencement endorsed is the same as the date of
                            commencement endorsed on the branch registration certificate;
                            or

paragraph.content:
where a valid business registration certificate has been issued in respect
                    of the business, by notice in writing given to the Commissioner not later than 1
                    month before the expiry date endorsed on the certificate;

where a business registration application for the business is made within 1
                    year of the commencement of the business, by a statement in the application;
                    or

subparagraph.content:
the election shall be irrevocable in respect of the first applicable
                        business registration certificate that has been or may be issued in respect
                        of the business after the election is made;

paragraph.content:
any prescribed business registration fee or prescribed branch registration
                    fee or any levy which is payable in respect of the business or the branch, as
                    the case may be, shall remain payable;

a notification of the withdrawal, removal or replacement of the general
                    partner in a limited partnership fund is filed under section 25(2) of
                    that Ordinance;

subparagraph.content:
the number of the identity card (as defined by section 1A(1)
                        of the Registration of Persons Ordinance (Cap.
                            177));

breeding or rearing livestock including dairy farming, poultry
                        including the production of eggs, bees including the production of honey, or
                        fish including crustaceans and oysters;

a former Companies Ordinance as defined by section 2(1)
                            of the Companies Ordinance (Cap.
                            622);
